<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><listPerson xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><person xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="HAM01" sex="1"><persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"><forename xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Archibald</forename><surname xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Hamilton</surname><addName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0"/></persName><birth xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1719"><placeName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Scotland</placeName></birth><death xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1793-03-09"/><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">printer</occupation><occupation xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">publisher</occupation><note xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="editorial"><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Hamilton became the publisher of the <title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Critical Review</title> in 1758 and took over the journal's editorship from Tobias Smollett in 1763. He was friendly with 
David Garrick, Samuel Johnson, and Oliver Goldsmith.</p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Although there are three Archibald Hamiltons, all of whom were printers, grandfather (d. 9 March 1793), father (who predeceases him, 6 October 1792) and two son (dates unknown: Archibald and Samuel), the identification 
can be ascertained by the entry of 28 Aug 1791 when Godwin notes
his age being 71 - corresponding with the <title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">DNB</title>.</p><p xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Hamilton appears with <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="ROB01">Robinson</persName>, <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="HOL01">Holcroft</persName> and 
  <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="NIC01">Nicholson</persName> but as the diary goes on the meetings seem to become less intimate and more related to business
(letters and calls instead of dinners). For entries after Archibald Hamilton's death see <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="HAM03">Samuel Hamilton</persName>.</p></note><bibl xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="other"><title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">DNB</title></bibl><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="appearancesInDiary"><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1788"><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-06-27" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-07-14" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-08-08" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-09-22" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-10-24" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-11-04" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-11-07" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-11-17" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-12-03" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1788-12-22" n="notVenue" type="ah"/></ab><ab xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" n="1789"><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1789-01-19" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1789-01-22" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1789-01-24" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1789-03-02" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1789-03-09" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1789-04-05" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1789-04-06" n="venue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" when="1789-06-08" n="notVenue" type="ah"/><date xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.